pull.title: contrib: Fix check-doc script regexes
pull.body:
Fixup the regexes to properly find all used args. The regex should now match all of the getter and setter methods of the `ArgsManager`. See https://dev.visucore.com/bitcoin/doxygen/class_args_manager.html#pub-methods

Before:
```
Args used        : 159
Args documented  : 188
Args undocumented: 0
Args unknown     : 29
```

After:
```
Args used        : 183
Args documented  : 188
Args undocumented: 0
Args unknown     : 5
```

events.body: You can disable the whitespace changes for review (e.g. on GitHub web view with https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/12820/commits/136084470cd7920b94e016621ebf682996247162?w=1)

Tested ACK 136084470cd7920b94e016621ebf682996247162

Looks like it works. We can remove the help text for the non-existent `-fuzzmessagestest` (removed in ea3326891d8c3dcbcff178b618108d657c5586a3)

events.message: init: Remove help text for non-existent -fuzzmessagestest arg

events.body: Oh, I wasn't suggesting we needed to do it here, but sure why not. Tested ACK 0c17e27630ada2d9284e357cc0e92ffff8775423
Concept ACK, eventually this script will be unnecessary when the arguments are registered alongside their help text btw
